@startuml
title Advanced Architecture Flow (Token Exchange)

actor "User's Browser" as Browser
participant "Client App\n(WebApp)" as WebApp
participant "Mid-Tier API\n(ApiA)" as ApiA
participant "Resource API\n(ApiB)" as ApiB
participant "Auth Server\n(OpenIddict)" as AuthServer

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam autnumber "<b>[0]</b>"

Browser -> WebApp: 1. Access root page (/)

activate WebApp
WebApp -> ApiA: 2. Request data from ApiA\n(GET /forward)

note right of WebApp
  `AccessTokenManagement`
  needs a token for "ApiA".
end note

activate ApiA
WebApp -> AuthServer: 3. Request Token A\n(grant_type: client_credentials, scope: api_a)
activate AuthServer
AuthServer --> WebApp: Return Token A
note right of AuthServer
  Issue Token A with presenters:
  [webapp_client, apia_client]
  so ApiA can legally exchange it later.
end note
deactivate AuthServer

note right of WebApp
  Token A is now cached.
end note

WebApp -> ApiA: 4. Re-issue request with Token A attached
note right of ApiA
  Middleware validates Token A.
  Now needs to call ApiB.
  `AccessTokenManagement` needs a token for "ApiB".
end note

ApiA -> AuthServer: 5. Exchange Token A for Token B\n(grant_type: token_exchange, subject_token: Token A)
activate AuthServer
AuthServer --> ApiA: Return Token B (with 'act' claim)
note right of AuthServer
  Validate subject_token_type.
  Validate presenter allowance.
  (apia_client allowed by Token A).
  Map scope(api_b) -> resource(api_b_resource).
  If scope metadata missing, fallback resource is set.
end note
deactivate AuthServer

note right of ApiA
  Token B is now cached.
end note

ApiA -> ApiB: 6. Request data from ApiB with Token B\n(GET /data)
activate ApiB

note right of ApiB
  Middleware validates Token B
  and checks 'act' claim.
end note

ApiB --> ApiA: 7. Return protected data
deactivate ApiB
ApiA --> WebApp: 8. Forward data from ApiB
deactivate ApiA
WebApp --> Browser: 9. Display final data
deactivate WebApp

@enduml